Waje has unveiled the visuals for her single Kponlongo featuring Timaya. The song is a smooth dancehall tune that tells the story of two lovers expressing their feelings without inhibitions. While the word Kponlongo itself means ‘loud’, the video, directed by Mex films, sets a very serene, sultry and intimate mood. Read More: Watch Wizkid And Skepta’s Video For “Bad Energy” The shimmery drapery in the background and the artiste’s undeniable chemistry with Timaya lends to the sensuality of the video and makes it difficult to ignore the connection we feel. Enjoy! 